      "id": "U3U-READ-1",
      "paper": "review",
      "title": "Leo's First Job",
      "text": "Leo is an active student in the Food and Beverage Department. Last summer he got a chance to work at a night market stall. The stall is famous for its cheese toast. On his first day, the owner told him to watch out for the hot oil. Leo felt worried, but he soon became familiar with the job. His work is simple. He takes each order, makes the toast, and cleans the tables. The pay is not high, so Leo will never build great wealth here. Still, he does not worry about it. He decided to save part of the money for a basketball camp. His parents' only concern is his health, because he sleeps late every night. Leo knows they are right. Next month he will choose an earlier shift."
    }
  ],
